<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-16T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-16T22:00:00-05:00" n="599" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/2061: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Childs</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-16T22:00:00-05:00">December 16, 1941—10
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>159. Your 372, November 28, 1 p.m. In view of the apparent
                                uncertainty of the precise purpose of the Delegate’s note, the
                                Department feels that the first and last paragraphs of your proposed
                                reply constitute an adequate acknowledgment and offer of
                                cooperation. However, it is suggested that in the last paragraph the
                                word “adjusting” be substituted for the phrase “my informal
                                endeavors to adjust”.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>